<sec>
<st>
 Currie Rose fund </st>
<p>

Carl J. B. Currie, a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../701/506701.xml">
trustee</link> and major benefactor to the hospital, noticed that while some patients received bouquets of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../465/4576465.xml">
flower</link>s from well-wishers to encourage their recovery, other patients received none.  In 1958 he established the Carl J. B. and Olive Currie Rose Fund to ensure that all patients would henceforth be welcomed with a red <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../537/26537.xml">
rose</link>, a tradition that continues today.  NEBH has since adopted the rose as its official symbol, indicative of the hospital’s commitment to high quality and individualized patient care.</p>

